Credit Suisse Group, Holcim: Swiss Equity Preview for Tuesday

-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 
2011-04-26T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/credit-suisse-group-holcim-swiss-equity-preview-for-tuesday.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share
prices are from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index (SMI)  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies gained 0.2 percent to 6,457.16. The broader
Swiss Performance Index rose 0.3 percent to 5,937.46.  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  : U.S. authorities may drop
charges against Credit Suisse banker Christos Bagios by May 12
over his alleged involvement in tax evasion, NZZ am Sonntag
reported, citing a document from the Fort Lauderdale district
court. The shares rose 0.8 percent to 38.85 Swiss francs.  Holcim Ltd. (HOLN)  : The cement maker is manufacturing at
close to capacity in Asia, NZZ am Sonntag reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Markus Akermann. The company will only benefit
“on the margins” from post-earthquake reconstruction in  Japan ,
the newspaper cited Akermann as saying. The shares rose 1.8
percent to 76 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net  